- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper focuses on cyber-physical systems from an automatic control perspective, which falls under the scope of this sub-category.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper specifically addresses security concerns in cyber-physical systems, making this sub-category a likely fit.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper may also be relevant to this sub-category as it discusses defense strategies and algorithms for securing cyber-physical systems.
- cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity): The paper's focus on cybersecurity and its potential consequences of failures make this sub-category a possible fit.
- cs.RO (Robotics): While not the main focus, the paper does mention robotics as one of the application fields for cyber-physical systems, making this sub-category a possible fit as well.
